# XDS Theme Color Design

## Palette Foundation

Every color in a theme must come from a defined HCT tonal palette. Each palette has:
- **Hue (H)**: fixed per color (e.g., Green=142, Blue=265)
- **Chroma (C)**: fixed per color — ONE value, used for both light and dark mode
- **Tone steps**: selected per usage (T90 for light bg, T70 for dark bg, etc.)

No ad-hoc hex values. If a color can't be traced to `hctToHex(H, C, T)` for a defined palette entry, it doesn't belong.

## Core Neutral Palette

All neutrals (body, surface, border, card, text, disabled, gray badge) MUST share one HCT hue. Verify by running `hexToHct()` on every neutral hex — the hue should be consistent (±2°).

## Categorical Colors

Define 9-10 hues with sufficient angular separation (minimum 15° between neighbors). Each gets ONE chroma value. Derive all tokens from tone steps:

| Token | Light Tone | Dark Tone |
|-------|-----------|-----------|
| Background | T90 | T70 |
| Text/Icon | T30 | T15 |
| Border | T85 | T65 |

## Semantic Colors

Map to categorical palettes — no separate colors:
- Success = Green palette
- Error = Red palette  
- Warning = Yellow palette

Use component overrides (`badge`, `banner`) to set semantic badge/banner colors. Use different tone steps from categoricals for visual hierarchy (e.g., T80 dark semantic vs T70 dark categorical).

## Component Overrides

Global tokens like `--color-success` serve multiple components (badge bg, input border, icon color). When these conflict, use component overrides in `defineTheme({ components: {} })` to scope colors per component. Use `light-dark()` for hardcoded light/dark values in overrides.

## Dark Mode

Don't invert light mode. Don't scale chroma differently between modes. Use the SAME palette (same H, same C) with different tone steps. Test dark badge backgrounds at multiple tones using a canvas before committing.

## Preview Page

Always preview with real XDS components (`XDSBadge`, `XDSBanner`, `XDSTextInput`, `XDSButton`), not hardcoded inline styles. Wrap each mode column in `<XDSTheme theme={theme} mode={mode}>`. Rebuild the theme (`npm run build`) before previewing — the built artifact must be current.

## Audit

After changes, verify every token traces back to the palette:
```
expectedHex = hctToHex(H, C, toneStep)
actualHex = theme token value
assert(expectedHex === actualHex)
```
